<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><title> Particular Solutions </title>

	<p>
		Now that we know what initial conditions are, let's discuss how they can be used to extract a particular solution from the family of solutions.
	</p>

	<p>
		Consider the differential equation
		<me> \frac{dy}{dx} = 2xy - 6x </me>,
		which has the general solution, <m> y = c_{1}e^{x^2} + 3. </m>
	</p>  

	<p>
		Since each member of the family of solutions comes from a different value of <m>c_{1}</m>, we can plot a few of them to see how they differ. The following graph shows the particular solutions for <m>c_{1} = -4, -3, -2, -1, -0.5, 0, 0.5, 1, 2, 3</m>.
	</p>
	
	<sidebyside widths="60%">
		<interactive xml:id="interactive-family" platform="jsxgraph" source="code/family-of-solutions.js">
			<slate xml:id="interactive-family-slate" surface="jsxboard"/>
		</interactive>			
	</sidebyside>
	
	<example><title> Apply the Initial Condition to the General Solution </title>
		<p>
			Given that the general solution to <m> \displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} = 2xy - 6x </m> is 
			<men xml:id="example-general-solution">y = c_{1}e^{x^2} + 3</men>, 
			find the particular solution that corresponds to the initial condition <m>y(0) = 2</m>.
		</p>
	
		<solution>
	
			<p>
				Since the condition <m>y(0) = 2</m> can be read "<m>y</m> equals 2 when <m>x</m> equals 0", we set <m>y=2</m> and <m>x=0</m> in the <xref ref="example-general-solution" text="custom"> general solution </xref>, and solve for <m>c_{1}</m>.
			</p>
		
			<p>
				<md>
					<mrow> y =  c_{1}e^{x^2} + 3 \quad \overset{y\ =\ 2,\ x\ =\ 0}{\Rightarrow} \quad	2	\amp=  c_{1}e^{0^2} + 3	</mrow>
					<mrow>							 													2	\amp=  c_{1} + 3		</mrow>
					<mrow>																				-1	\amp=  c_{1}			</mrow>
				</md>
			</p>
		
			<p>
				Plugging this <m>c_1</m> into the <xref ref="example-general-solution" text="custom"> general solution </xref> gives the particular solution
				<me>y = -e^{x^2} + 3</me>.
			</p>
	
		</solution>
	
	</example>

	<interactive xml:id="interactive-drag-ic" platform="jsxgraph" source="code/initial-condition.js">
